    "A key question then is how this is modified for k > 1, where any such connection to twistor space is less well understood.As a final comment on the free field interpretation for the Wakimoto representation, we note that the insertionsδ(S) = δ e -2Φβ have many qualities in common with the secret representations of [4].",
    "Another candidate is the related non-local operator S:= e iκ 2, discussed around (2.23).",
    "Like δ(S), S is invariant under SL(2) and has the correct behaviour at the spurious poles [K, S] = 2 S. The insertions S carry precisely the charge needed to balance the conformal anomaly.",
